name: Mount Rainier Day Hike
description:
If you love adventure and getting out and experiencing the real outdoors, then this hike is for you.

This is a semi-private guided hike on the Three Burroughs Trail at Mount Rainier National Park. The hike is approximately six miles and winds through the high subalpine tundra above tree line and then down through mountain meadows. Offering wide open mountain views and a plethora of wildflowers.

review.name: An amazing experience with a great guide!
review.reviewBody:
Absolutely wonderful group of people to do this with! So unbelievably happy I came across them when I was planning our trip. Great communication throughout the entire process. Our guide, Josh, was very personable and knowledgeable. I loved all the information - historical, geological, and biological - that he provided during the trip from the time he picked us up. (Because if you're like me, curious minds want to know.)
We did the Burroughs trail. The hike is amazing, with breathtaking views of Mount Rainier. The sun and heat that day made the hike more challenging for me, as my body doesn't deal well with either, but Josh was patient and I was never made to feel like a burden. And the challenge made the reward all that more amazing.
The stop for ice cream after was the perfect finishing touch! (If you need an extra energy boost after the hike, the ice cream store also makes a tasty NA red bull spritzer.)
As someone who travels a lot, it's not often you find a business where your experience is flawless from start to finish. Thanks for making one of my bucket list ✔️  one of my all-time favorite hikes!

review.name: Awesome guided hiking experience
review.reviewBody:
I was looking for a guided hike that would take care of all logistics and was stoked to have found Adventures in Seattle! I used Sophia's services for a guided hike in Mt. Rainier and I couldn't have been happier with the experience!

Sophia was wonderful throughout the entire process. Prior to booking she was incredibly kind & responsive and after booking she was very communicative in confirming the details we'd need to know regarding weather, pickup, etc. Finally, during the actual hike itself, she continuously made sure everyone felt comfortable throughout the hike and worked to ensure everyone's safety. 

It was a memorable experience and would 100% recommend booking with her! Also, she keeps groups small, which was an added bonus!

review.name: Everything You Could Want For a Day Hike
review.reviewBody:
I was very fortunate, in many capacities, to have Sophia as a guide for a three person tour to The Three Burroughs in an attempt to see the best views of Mt. Rainier.

The guide experience with Sophia was more like traveling with a highly experienced friend rather than an overly sanitized, corporate excursion. I mean this is the best possible way — Adventures in Seattle offered wonderful personal services like pick-up from any Seattle lodging, food recommendations for the included lunch, backpacks in case we didn't want ours to get wet, and hiking poles for the day, all of which were a part of the trip cost and are not very common.

The weather did not cooperate for us. What should have been a cloudy day with decent rain on the mountains rapidly became gale-force winds pelting us with painful sleet as we reached higher elevations. Sophia was willing to push when I said I wanted to keep going, and we did, until our waterproof hiking boots and pants were soaked through and it became clear to her we were reaching dangerous territory. And so, we turned back. Had I been alone I don't think I would have — this would have been to my detriment. It wasn't until we were in safer parts of the hike that I realized how bad it really was. This is why a guide is important for inexperienced mountain hikers, and we were lucky to have Sophia there. Hubris on a mountain is not an asset.

And still! Still! This was an incredibly fun hike. We got to see Mt. Rainier's glaciers, some gorgeous lakes and wildflowers, accompanied by unparalleled views and a perfect amount of history and general knowledge shared by Sophia. I will recommend Adventures in Seattle to anyone and everyone coming out to Washington.

review.name: Awesome hike
review.reviewBody: Fantastic experience! The views were amazing. Matt was very knowledgeable.  Definitely recommended.

review.name: Epic Hike!
review.reviewBody: Sophia led the hike up the Burroughs trail  and it was incredible. I went solo and she worked me into a small group of three others and let me just say, we had a Blast!! She provided transportation to and from the trail which makes it really convenient if you do not have a rental car. She made sure everyone was properly prepared for the day, managed the pace of hike, provided great snacks, and a hearty lunch. It was just so well organized. Mt Rainier was shining that day which made the trip even more special.  We also saw mountain goats, marmots, pikas, even a sow and cub.  The park is just so beautiful and Sophia made sure we had a great experience. This was absolutely the highlight of my trip. I highly recommend "Adventures in Seattle"!! I will be booking another adventure with Sophia when I get back to the area!

review.name: Mount Rainier Day Hike - August 2020
review.reviewBody: Wow!  You are going to love this hike with “Adventures In Seattle”!  Both Sophia and Kevin are cool people who make you feel welcome and appreciated. Sophia was very accommodating and well organized in helping me understand what to expect. Kevin took me on the hike to Mount Rainier National Park, and it was like a non-stop conversation from pick-up to drop-off.  Kevin is so down to earth, knowledgeable, and has so many interesting stories from his experiences outdoors.  The hike itself captures the beauty of the National Park and Mount Rainier and it is timed and organized perfectly.  Kevin is very knowledgeable of the Park itself, but he also gave pointers on the skill and technique of hiking, which is a takeaway I can use when hiking in other areas.  The hike itself was, in my opinion, a notch above “moderate” in skill level.  When we completed the hike, I feel like I accomplished something and felt good about myself.  I highly recommend this hike (or anything else from “Adventures In Seattle”) and look forward to another adventure with them during my next visit to Seattle!

review.name: Meticulously Planned trip
review.reviewBody: It was a beautiful 9 mile hike I was on with another family of mother and daughter. Sophia took very good care of us and planned it extremely well always attending to our needs and food requirements. Thank you so much Sophia!

review.name: Amazing experience !
review.reviewBody: My mom and I completed a 9 mile hike with Sophia and one other traveler. We had the most amazing day. Sophia was very kind, sociable and provided everything needed for the day hike. She was very accommodating with regards to dietary restrictions and made a delicious vegan lunch. Overall a wonderful experience and would reccomend to anyone seeking a fun and adventurous day trip out of Seattle !

review.name: Amazing Experience
review.reviewBody: Me and my college aged daughter did a 9 mile day hike with Sophia and one other guest at Mount Rainier. Every part of the day was well planned and extremely enjoyable. Sophia was very kind, social and hospitable. She was very accommodating even with my daughters many dietary restrictions in which she made a delicious vegan lunch and brought many snacks for the hike. This was a very enjoyable experience and I would recommend Adventures in Seattle to anyone looking for a personal and adventurous Seattle experience. Thank you Sophia !

review.name: Beautiful views
review.reviewBody:
I have done 2 hikes with this group and both provided beautiful views! The first hike was Mount Rainier Three Burroughs. I would recommend this hike to those who are in good physical condition as it was a bit rough. I consider myself to be in average/above average condition but I live at sea level and at that elevation it was more difficult for me to breathe and I needed to make frequent stops on the inclines (which our guides were great about stopping and making sure we were comfortable). While I wasn't sore after this, if you aren't used to hiking, be prepared for a bit of soreness. With all of that being said, the views are just gorgeous so it makes it totally worth it!! You can see so much on a clear day!!!

The 2nd hike was called Talapus Lake. This was an easy ~4 mi round-trip hike. The lake is crystal clear and is great for swimming and fishing or just relaxing. We stopped at the first lake but you can extend your journey by hiking to the next lake, just ask your knowledgeable hostess, Sophia to take you there.  

I can not say enough good things about Sophia. She is very knowledgeable about the area and about hiking. She will go out of her way to make sure that your experience is everything you hoped it to be and more.

The game is played on an app and instructs you to find a variety of items (given in riddle form) that can be found in the downtown area of the city. For every item you find, you'll get points. itemListElement.name: Hike into the Salish Sea: Dungeness Spit

name: Hike into the Salish Sea: Dungeness Spit
description:
Dungeness Spit is one of the world’s longest sand spits, gracefully curving 5 miles into the Salish Sea, where the Strait of Juan de Fuca ends and Admiralty Inlet to Puget Sound begins, climaxing at the historic New Dungeness Lighthouse.

The spit comprises the Dungeness Wildlife Refuge, where waterfowl and marine animals abound.

This adventure involves hiking on a sandy (and sometimes rocky) surface from the trailhead to the lighthouse in 10 almost entirely flat miles round-trip.

itemListElement.name: Mt. Rainier Tour From Downtown Seattle

name: Mt. Rainier Tour From Downtown Seattle
description:
Join us on our day to visit Mt. Rainier National Park where you can enjoy walking amongst old growth forests and meadows with the opportunity to see wildlife and wildflowers while looking towards the massive glaciers that keep Mt. Rainier perpetually white throughout all seasons. 

Your visit to the Paradise Jackson Visitor Center will allow you to have multiple options whether you want to take a hike up the trails or to Narada Falls or merely enjoy the view and the interpretive center to learn more about this majestic peak and the surrounding area. With adequate time to take in all the beauty and you won't feel rushed.

Your tour will have a stop at beautiful Christine Falls as well as Reflection Lake where you can photograph Mt. Rainier at one of the most picturesque locations in the Pacific Northwest. 

Our final stop will take us to Scaleburgers where you can purchase their famous hand-dipped chocolate shakes or taste their tasty "Overload" burger.

review.name: Mt Rainier with the best tour guides
review.reviewBody:
Took a long day trip to Mt Rainier with Shutter Tours. I had to drive into Seattle from the suburbs where i was staying. Parking was nearby and fairly reasonable.

Amanda, our guide for the day, was waiting with the bus (a 12-seater, I think) at 6:45am. The bus was pretty full but there was plenty of room for us to keep our gear around us.

As we took off Amanda told us about our schedule, including rest stops, photo op stops,  etc. All along the way she pointed out landmarks,  gave us short history lessons, and easily answered any and all questions. 

Once we arrived at Paradise we were on our own for 2 hours to either hike to a myriad of scenic places with fabulous views, take advantage of both indoor and outdoor programs offered by the park rangers, or do nothing but eat lunch and sit outside enjoying the views.

There were more stops along the way back down the mountain to see some spectacular water falls. 

Aside from a last stop for food, the trip back to Seattle was non-stop. We arrived at the starting point around 5:30pm. A long but exhilarating day. 

There was apparently a huge biking event up and over the mountain that day. This meant that Amanda had to negotiate the trip up the mountain around hundreds of bikers scattered all along the route.  She did a magnificent job.  Excellent driver.

I highly recommend Shutter Tours for a trip to Mt Rainier from Seattle. I have been to Rainier before but there is nothing like leaving the driving to them and having plenty of time to hike on some of the trails.

review.name: My. Rainier National Park Day Tour
review.reviewBody:
My wife and I spent the day with 9 other people and our driver/guide Amanda. Amanda was great, making sure we were all comfortable and that we understood how the tour would progress; e.g., where we would stop and for how long, where the bathroom breaks and food would be found, etc. 

It’s over 2 hours from downtown Seattle to the park, but the van is comfortable and Amanda filled the time with information about the park, its history, animals, plants, weather, etc., while allowing time for the tour group to get acquainted. 

The stops at various points in the park were well planned out. At each point, we had time to explore on our own, particularly at noon when we had 2 hours to dine, hike, watch a film, or just relax in the beautiful surroundings. Wildflowers galore. Amanda taught us some tricks to get better waterfall photos with our phones. 

The ride back was restful and many of us slept!

review.name: Mt. Rainier Day Tour
review.reviewBody: A great way to visit Mt. Rainier, whether you are a tourist or reside in Seattle.  Amanda is an incredible tour guide.  She is an experienced guide who is knowledgeable about the sights and history; professional while warm and welcoming; and an excellent driver.  The tour is well structured and Amanda kept us moving at just the right pace - staying on schedule, while still having ample time to enjoy the highlights of the Park and nearby sights.  This tour is a very good option for those traveling with a variety of ages and activity levels.  For example, in our group, we had two active middle-aged adults, plus one moderately active 75 year old, and one 5 year old, neither of whom were very interested in hiking much.  This tour would not be a good option for experienced hikers or those who would want to linger for extended periods in any part of the Park.  We love that it departed from downtown Seattle, and that we didn't have to do the drive ourselves.  My main suggestion is that you pack lunch or purchase it at the grocery store, when the tour makes that initial stop for bathroom and snacks at the Fred Meyer.  While the 75 year old seemed to enjoy the buffet brunch at the Paradise Lodge, it took more time and was pricier than we expected.  Again, certain people may want a comfortable place to sit inside for a while.  However, I recommend you bring your own food and drinks so you have lots of time to enjoy Paradise and the natural beauty outside.  I note that this was our second tour with Shutter Tours.  We also did the Tulip Festival.  Both experiences were fantastic for our family.  Thank you, Shutter Tours!

review.name: Rainier Summer Tour
review.reviewBody: One of the best tours I’ve had. Our driver/guide was very professional and enthusiastic. There were plenty of stops for     bathroom breaks/food. I strongly recommend it. The views were incredible.
